<db:titleabbrev>QtScriptTools Reference Documentation</db:titleabbrev>
<db:abstract>
<db:para>Provides a debugger for applications that use Qt Script.</db:para>
</db:abstract>
<db:pubdate>2025-06-29</db:pubdate>
<db:date>2025-06-29</db:date>
<db:authorgroup>
<db:author>
<db:orgname class="corporation">The Qt Company Ltd.</db:orgname>
</db:author>
</db:authorgroup>
</db:info>
<db:para>The Qt Script Tools module provides a debugger that can be embedded into Qt applications that use <db:link xlink:href="qtscript-index.xml">Qt Script</db:link>. The debugger enables the application user to inspect the state of the script environment and control script execution.</db:para>
<db:section xml:id="configuring-the-build-process">
<db:title>Configuring the Build Process</db:title>
<db:para>To include the definitions of the module's classes, use the following directive:</db:para>
<db:programlisting language="cpp">#include &lt;QtScriptTools&gt;
</db:programlisting>
<db:para>To link against the module, add this line to your <db:link xlink:href="qmake-manual.xml">qmake</db:link> <db:code>.pro</db:code> file:</db:para>
<db:programlisting language="cpp">QT += scripttools
</db:programlisting>
